FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:
The functional requirements ensures what is going to be functional on each page or website in general.

Example:
Home page: The system should have  a home page that consists of the nav bar, main section and footer.

Another example:
User management
	Users can create, update and delete accounts
	Role-based access control for different user types(Homeowners, business, owners, service providers etc.)
	Multi-factor authentication for enhanced security

Consultation and installation scheduling:
	Users can view available time slots and book consultations
	Automated appointment reminders and rescheduling options
	integration with service provider calendars for real-time availability

