NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:
The non-functional requirements ensures what is going to be non-functional on each page or website in general.

Example:
The Security should be secure and robust:
	system must validate all data inputs
	system must use secure cookies
	system must use SHA256 Encryption for the passwords

Another Example:
Performance and scalability:
	the platform must handle a high number of concurrent users without lag
	cloud-based architecture to support scalability as user demand increases
	load balancing to distribute traffic efficiently

Security and data protection:
	Compliance with data privacy regulation(GDPR, CCPA)
	Encryption of sensitive user information and secure authentication methods
	Regular security audits and vulnerabilities assessments

maintainability and support
	regular software updates to enhance features and security
	customer support via chat, email and phone for user assistance
	Comprehensive documentation for troubleshooting and user guidance


